The rocket strike against the US embassy in Athens has revived fears of extreme- left violence, never completely eradicated despite the break-up of Greece "'s" main radical groups earlier this decade.
The new group "'s" most brazen coup came in May 2004, when three homemade bombs exploded outside an Athens district police station at a time of high security for the Athens Games, an attack timed to coincide with the 100-day countdown to the Olympics.
